<subSubSection id="C33CA9C7FFA7FFD0A559F7D4B56CCB40" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B99FA4CFFA7FFD0A559F7D4B56CCB40" blockId="3.[2075,2667,1824,2247]" lastBlockId="3.[1462,2666,2254,2681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis id="B952265EFFA7FFD0A559F7D4B63CCA7F" bold="true" box="[2075,2356,2056,2089]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 161-191 mm (males) and 162-191 mm (females), tail 16-23 mm (males) and 17-25 mm (females). No specific data are available for body weight. The Nigerian Mole-rat is medium-sized, with white markings on its body and a head patch; its pelage is brown,soft, and fine. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 66 or 70, FN = 126 or 134.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
